article.headline: Northern Iowa 79, Upper Iowa University 68
article.story: FAYETTE, Iowa (AP) -- Matt Hammer led four double-figure scorers with 19 points as the Northern State Wolves, ranked 13th in Division II basketball, defeated Upper Iowa 73-57 on Monday. Hammer also led the squad with six rebounds. Craig Nelson and Adam Grant each contributed 11 points for Northern (17-2). Bjoern Schoo added 10. Upper Iowa (2-21) was paced by 17 points from Marcus Uhlenhopp. Turmel Woods scored 13 and Nick Larson 12. The Wolves made 19 of 26 free throws, while Upper Iowa shot 12 for the game, converting only five.
